  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\r\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \r\n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\r\n<!--     https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/master/CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md -->\r\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\r\n<!--   * Read the debugging wiki: https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/wiki/debugging -->\r\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3Ahyperledger/Besu -->\r\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nAs documented at Ethereum wiki https://eth.wiki/json-rpc/API, JSON-RPC method net_version should return network ID instead of chain ID. For Ethereum Classic, the Chain ID is 61 and network ID is 1. Core-Geth, Multi-Geth, OpenEthereum all returns 1 for the RPC call. However, Hyperledger Besu returns 61 which is the Chain ID instead of the network ID.  \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* [Criteria 1]\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\nCore-Geth: \r\n```\r\n>>> curl -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"net_version\",\"params\":[],\"id\":67}' http://core-geth/rpc\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":67,\"result\":\"1\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nMulti-Geth:\r\n```\r\n>>> curl -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"net_version\",\"params\":[],\"id\":67}' http://multi-geth/rpc\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":67,\"result\":\"1\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOpenEthereum: \r\n```\r\n>>> curl -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"net_version\",\"params\":[],\"id\":67}' http://parity/rpc\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"result\":\"1\",\"id\":67}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd Hyperledger Besu: \r\n```\r\n>>> curl -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"net_version\",\"params\":[],\"id\":67}' http://hyperledger-besu/rpc\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\" : \"2.0\",\r\n  \"id\" : 67,\r\n  \"result\" : \"61\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\n`net_version` returns 1 instead of 61 for network Ethereum Classic\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\n`net_version` returns 61 for network Ethereum Classic, which is the chain ID\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: [`besu --version`] 1.5.1\r\n* Java version: [`java -version`] 11\r\n* OS Name & Version: [`cat /etc/*release`] openjdk:11-jre-slim-buster\r\n* Kernel Version: [`uname -a`]\r\n* Virtual Machine software & version: [`vmware -v`]\r\n* Docker Version: [`docker version`]\r\n* Cloud VM, type, size: [Amazon Web Services I3-large]\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\nhttps://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/732cfcccc919f80db4150ccc4767f6b7fed63fa5/ethereum/api/src/main/java/org/hyperledger/besu/ethereum/api/jsonrpc/internal/methods/NetVersion.java It should be pretty straight forward to fix. Just make this class store/return networkId instead of chainId.\r\n",
